<HEADLINE>
FT  29 AUG 92 / Markets: At a Glance - Latin American trust has a mixed
first half
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Latin American Investment Trust, the best performing trust of 1991, had much
more volatile markets to deal with in the first half of 1992. The Brazilian
stock market, for example, jumped 90.1 per cent in the first four months of
the year but then dropped so sharply that the total rise for the first half
was just 1.3 per cent. The trust's net asset per share increased 4.5 per
cent to Dollars 1.85 over the six months to June 30.
