<HEADLINE>
FT  28 AUG 92 / International Company News: Pasminco loses ADollars 58.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN BROWN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PASMINCO, the Australian lead and zinc group, blamed lower metals prices for
a net loss of ADollars 58.6m (USDollars 41.9m) for the year to the end of
June, against a loss of ADollars 47.6m the previous year.
Revenue fell from ADollars 1.5bn to ADollars 1.3bn, largely reflecting falls
of 11 per cent and 23 per cent in the average prices of zinc and lead on
world markets.
The loss was in line with the group's warning last month, which coincided
with the partial unwinding of an 80.6 per cent joint shareholding formerly
held by North Broken Hill Peko (North) and CRA, the Australian mining
groups.
Pasminco said the figure included an abnormal loss of ADollars 15.4m,
reflecting rationalisation costs and a tax charge of ADollars 12.5m
following a tax audit of 1985 to 1988 accounts. Bottom line loss rose to
ADollars 140.1m after including a net extraordinary loss of ADollars 81.5m
relating to the writedown of the Elura mine in New South Wales.
There is no dividend.
</TEXT>
