FT  28 AUG 92 / Court quashes Bond conviction
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN BROWN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE long-running Alan Bond show was back on the road yesterday after the
Western Australian Court of Criminal Appeal quashed a fraud conviction
against the bankrupt Australian entrepreneur.
An emotional Mr Bond was collected by his son John from Wooroloo open
prison, near Perth, shortly after the verdict. Fighting back tears he said
