</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NEIL BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE REMOVAL of distortions in the energy market could cut emissions of
carbon dioxide in the UK by 40 per cent and put money back into the economy,
says a study published today by environmental pressure group Friends of the
Earth.
The report says failure to take action would mean market distortions
continuing to misdirect Pounds 2bn a year on investment in uneconomic and
carbon-intensive technologies.
Friends of the Earth's proposals include linking mortgage tax relief to
energy efficiency in the home and a carbon tax.
Efficiency Without Tears. Friends of the Earth, 26-28 Underwood St, London
