FT  28 AUG 92 / Shots fired at policeman after City bank raid
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
ARMED bank robbers yesterday opened fire on a police officer during a chase
in the City of London.
It happened after two men armed with handguns escaped with a small amount of
cash from the Royal Bank of Scotland in Great Tower Street, near the Tower
of London, late yesterday morning. A passing police motor-cyclist saw the
robbers and chased them to Southwark Bridge, where they stopped their car
and opened fire. The car moved on before stopping halfway across the bridge
where the gunmen fired more shots.
The raiders' white Vauxhall Astra car, driven by a third man, was later
found abandoned near Hays Galleria at London Bridge.
Southwark Bridge was closed to traffic briefly while police officers
searched the area for spent cartridges.
City of London police said the unarmed PC, who was not named, was 'shaken
up' but uninjured. They added that the British Bankers' Association had put
up a Pounds 15,000 reward for information leading to the capture of the
gang.
They appealed for witnesses to the incident to contact Bishopsgate CID on
071-601 2670.
